      • getNormalizedLocation

        public VertexLocation getNormalizedLocation()
        Returns a canonical (i.e., unique) value for this vertex location. Since each vertex has three different locations on a map, this method converts a vertex location to a single canonical form. This is useful for using vertex locations as map keys.
        Returns:
        Normalized vertex location
